result.text:
I didn’t think it was possible, but @jynxzi has singlehanded made Clash Royale the most popular it has ever been in 3 years after a devastating update.

Creators are having their most popular videos they’ve had in ages because of collabs, and millions of new eyes are on the game due to him streaming it. 

This is more significant than when @xQc and @ishowspeedsui played Clash Royale. They were mindlessly playing cards and mostly did it as a joke and their audience thought nothing much of the game.

Jynxzi on the other hand is actively collaborating and engaging with the pro scene and actively trying to improve showcasing the true competitive nature and strategy of the game while keeping his fun, energetic, and entertaining personality which appeals to casuals too.

Supercell should capitalize on this amazing opportunity and momentum and be motivated to bring the best update we’ve seen in ages. The prize pool and even world finalist player count should even be considered being increased in CRL with the new hype and players checking out the game. They can’t let this potential go to waste.
